				<div class="body">
					<p>Not completely sure I buy into #4, but I see where you are coming from, and I like the rest.</p>
<p>In a few situations I use the same view file for a couple of actions, and it is useful to change the pageTitle in the controller method to modify. It's really convenient to do it that way for those pages (add/edit methods using the same view for example). It seemed more elegant and easier to recognise for others in the future to do this via $this->pageTitle than a separate $this->set('title' ....) Perhaps it is not entirely MVC but I can let that one go.</p>
<p>For the add/edit example, to get around this it is possible to look at the action name and work that into the pageTitle anyway .... ( essentially do something like $this->pageTitle = $this->action . " Item" etc ... )</p>
				</div>
